<li id="cite_note-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53" title="">^</a></b> Justus Reid Weiner, "'My Beautiful Old House' and Other Fabrications by Edward Said," <i><a href="/wiki/Commentary_(magazine)" title="Commentary (magazine)">Commentary</a></i>; abridged versions and extracts or excerpts of Weiner's article were also published elsewhere, incl. in both <i><a href="/wiki/The_Daily_Telegraph" title="The Daily Telegraph">The Daily Telegraph</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wall_Street_Journal" title="The Wall Street Journal">The Wall Street Journal</a></i>; see, e.g., Justus Reid Weiner, "The False Prophet of Palestine" <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wall_Street_Journal" title="The Wall Street Journal">The Wall Street Journal</a> <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1999-08-26"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="08-26"><a href="/wiki/August_26" title="August 26">August 26</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1999" title="1999">1999</a></span>.</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54" title="">^</a></b> Rpt. in Michael Sprinkler, ed. <i>Edward Said: A Critical Reader</i> (London: Blackwell, 1993). <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/155786229X" class="internal">ISBN 1-55786-229-X</a>. Some say it was acknowledged as early as 1989</li>
<li id="cite_note-55"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55" title="">^</a></b> Qtd. in <a href="http://www.counterpunch.org/said1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.counterpunch.org/said1.html" rel="nofollow">"Commentary: 'Scholar' Deliberately Falsified Record in Attack on Said,"</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Counterpunch_(newsletter)" title="Counterpunch (newsletter)" class="mw-redirect">Counterpunch</a></i> <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1999-09-01"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="09-01"><a href="/wiki/September_1" title="September 1">September 1</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1999" title="1999">1999</a></span>, accessed <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2006-02-10"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-10"><a href="/wiki/February_10" title="February 10">February 10</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56" title="">^</a></b> Edward Said, <a href="http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/1999/444/op2.htm" class="external text" title="http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/1999/444/op2.htm" rel="nofollow">"Defamation, Zionist-style,"</a> <i>Al-Ahram Weekly</i> August 26 - Sept. 1 1999, accessed <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2006-02-10"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-10"><a href="/wiki/February_10" title="February 10">February 10</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a></span>.</li>
